<TITLE> BCL leader hacked at Brahmanbaria </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Brahmanbaria, July 8 (bdnews24.com)A leader of Brahmanbaria chapter of pro-Awami League Bangaldesh Chhatra League, was hacked by unknown assailants late on Tuesday night. A group of criminals barged into the office of the firm Mithila Trading of Atikur Rahman Apu, 29, the vice president of Brahmanbaria district BCL, at College Para in the town at around 11:45pm. They ransacked the office and hacked him with sharp weapons, said Rezaul Karim Bhuiyan, officer-in-charge of Brahmanbaria Sadar Police Station. The criminals shot four rounds of bullets before running away, said Abu Taher, a local resident. Apu has been admitted to Brahmanbari Sadar hospital in a critical state. A police team led by assistant police superintendent (Sadar circle) Nazmul Hasan carried out a drive at Kandipara of the town after the incident. Hasan said they were trying to arrest the assailants. The attack was a consequence of internal clash, said police. Residents of the area are living in fear after the incident. 
